      "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b><a href=\"/Main_Page\" title=\"Main Page\">Home</a> * <a href=\"/Periodical\" title=\"Periodical\">Periodical</a> * Byte Magazine</b>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:123px;\"><a href=\"https://archive.org/details/byte-magazine-1979-11\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/0/0f/BYTE_281-front.gif\" width=\"121\" height=\"161\" class=\"thumbimage\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/File:BYTE_281-front.gif\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>BYTE <sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></div></div></div> \n<p><b>Byte Magazine</b>, (BYTE)<br />\na monthly <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Microcomputer\">microcomputer</a> periodical, published from September 1975 until July 1998 <sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>. In spring of 1979, owner/publisher BYTE Publications, Inc., Virginia Williamson sold the magazine to <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/McGraw-Hill\">McGraw-Hill</a>. The readership of Byte and advertising revenue were declining when McGraw-Hill sold the magazine to <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/UBM_plc\">CMP Media</a>, who ceased publication with the July 1998 issue. Specially Volume 3, 1978 has various computer chess related articles. Most BYTE Magazines are available in the <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Internet_Archive\">Internet Archive</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>. \n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Selected_Authors\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Selected Authors</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Chess_Programs\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Chess Programs</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Selected_Articles\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Selected Articles</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Volume_3_1978\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Volume 3 1978</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-3 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Vol._3.2C_No._1.2C_January_1978\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Vol. 3, No. 1, January 1978</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-3 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Vol._3.2C_No._3.2C_March_1978\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Vol. 3, No. 3, March 1978</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-3 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#Vol._3.2C_No._7.2C_July.2C_1978\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Vol. 3, No. 7, July, 1978</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-3 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#Vol._3.2C_No._9.2C_September_1978\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1.4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Vol. 3, No. 9, September 1978</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-3 tocsection-9\"><a href=\"#Vol._3.2C_No._10.2C_October_1978\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1.5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Vol. 3, No. 10, October 1978</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-3 tocsection-10\"><a href=\"#Vol._3.2C_No._11.2C_November_1978\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1.6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Vol. 3, No. 11, November 1978</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-3 tocsection-11\"><a href=\"#Vol._3.2C_No._12.2C_December_1978\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1.7</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Vol. 3, No. 12, December 1978</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-12\"><a href=\"#Volume_4_1979\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Volume 4 1979</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-3 tocsection-13\"><a href=\"#Vol._4.2C_No._1.2C_January.2C_1979\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Vol. 4, No. 1, January, 1979</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-3 tocsection-14\"><a href=\"#Vol._4.2C_No._11.2C_November_1979\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.2.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Vol. 4, No. 11, November 1979</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-15\"><a href=\"#Volume_11_1986\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Volume 11 1986</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-3 tocsection-16\"><a href=\"#Vol._11.2C_No._12.2C_November_1986\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Vol. 11, No. 12, November 1986</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-17\"><a href=\"#Volume_22_1997\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Volume 22 1997</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-3 tocsection-18\"><a href=\"#Vol._22.2C_No._7.2C_July_1997\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.4.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Vol. 22, No. 7, July 1997</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-19\"><a href=\"#External_Links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External Links</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-20\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Selected_Authors\">Selected Authors</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Byte_Magazine&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Selected Authors\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a href=\"/Larry_Atkin\" title=\"Larry Atkin\">Larry Atkin</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Peter_W._Frey\" title=\"Peter W. Frey\">Peter W. Frey</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Steve_Ciarcia\">Steve Ciarcia</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/index.php?title=Tom_R._Halfhill&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Tom R. Halfhill (page does not exist)\">Tom R. Halfhill</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Peter_Jennings\" title=\"Peter Jennings\">Peter Jennings</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/index.php?title=Peter_B._Maggs&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Peter B. Maggs (page does not exist)\">Peter B. Maggs</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Ward_Douglas_Maurer\" title=\"Ward Douglas Maurer\">Ward Douglas Maurer</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Dan_Spracklen\" title=\"Dan Spracklen\">Dan Spracklen</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Kathe_Spracklen\" title=\"Kathe Spracklen\">Kathe Spracklen</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Norman_Whaland\" title=\"Norman Whaland\">Norman Whaland</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.devili.iki.fi/library/author/1504.en.html\">James M. Williams</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Chess_Programs\">Chess Programs</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Byte_Magazine&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Chess Programs\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a href=\"/Boris\" title=\"Boris\">Boris</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Chess_(Program)\" title=\"Chess (Program)\">Chess</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Chess_0.5\" title=\"Chess 0.5\">Chess 0.5</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Dark_Horse\" title=\"Dark Horse\">Dark Horse</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Deep_Blue\" title=\"Deep Blue\">Deep Blue</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/El_Ajedrecista\" title=\"El Ajedrecista\">El Ajedrecista</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Kaissa\" title=\"Kaissa\">Kaissa</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/MicroChess\" title=\"MicroChess\">MicroChess</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Sargon\" title=\"Sargon\">Sargon</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Selected_Articles\">Selected Articles</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Byte_Magazine&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Selected Articles\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<p><span id=\"BYTE301\"></span>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Volume_3_1978\">Volume 3 1978</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Byte_Magazine&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: Volume 3 1978\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Vol._3.2C_No._1.2C_January_1978\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://archive.org/details/byte-magazine-1978-01\">Vol. 3, No. 1, January 1978</a></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Byte_Magazine&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: Vol. 3, No. 1, January 1978\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:123px;\"><a href=\"https://archive.org/details/byte-magazine-1978-01\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/2/2b/BYTE_246-front.gif\" width=\"121\" height=\"162\" class=\"thumbimage\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/File:BYTE_246-front.gif\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Vol. 3, No. 1</div></div></div>\n<ul><li> <a href=\"/Peter_Jennings\" title=\"Peter Jennings\">Peter Jennings</a> (<b>1978</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://archive.org/stream/byte-magazine-1978-01/1978_01_BYTE_03-01_The_Brains_of_Men_and_Machines#page/n107/mode/2up\">The Second World Computer Chess Championships - Where KAISSA Founders on a Bug and CHESS 4.6 Conquers All</a></i>.&#160;» <a href=\"/WCCC_1977\" title=\"WCCC 1977\">WCCC 1977</a>, <a href=\"/Kaissa\" title=\"Kaissa\">Kaissa</a>, <a href=\"/Chess_(Program)\" title=\"Chess (Program)\">Chess</a></li></ul>\n<p><span id=\"BYTE303\"></span>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Vol._3.2C_No._3.2C_March_1978\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://archive.org/details/byte-magazine-1978-03\">Vol. 3, No. 3, March 1978</a></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Byte_Magazine&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: Vol. 3, No. 3, March 1978\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<ul><li> <a href=\"/Peter_Jennings\" title=\"Peter Jennings\">Peter Jennings</a> (<b>1978</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://archive.org/stream/byte-magazine-1978-03/1978_03_BYTE_03-03_Computer_Music_Systems#page/n167/mode/2up\">Microchess 1.5 Versus Dark Horse</a></i>.&#160;» <a href=\"/MicroChess\" title=\"MicroChess\">MicroChess</a>, <a href=\"/Dark_Horse\" title=\"Dark Horse\">Dark Horse</a></li></ul>\n<p><span id=\"BYTE307\"></span>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Vol._3.2C_No._7.2C_July.2C_1978\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://archive.org/details/byte-magazine-1978-07\">Vol. 3, No. 7, July, 1978</a></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Byte_Magazine&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" title=\"Edit section: Vol. 3, No. 7, July, 1978\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.amazon.com/The-BYTE-Book-Computer-Music/dp/0070430977\">Chris Morgan</a> (<b>1978</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://blog.modernmechanix.com/the-second-west-coast-computer-faire/1/#mmGal\">The Second West Coast Computer Faire</a></i>. <sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>&#160;» <a href=\"/MCCT_1978\" title=\"MCCT 1978\">MCCT 1978</a>, <a href=\"/Sargon\" title=\"Sargon\">Sargon</a>, <a href=\"/SD_Chess\" title=\"SD Chess\">SD Chess</a></li></ul>\n<p><span id=\"BYTE309\"></span>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Vol._3.2C_No._9.2C_September_1978\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://archive.org/details/byte-magazine-1978-09\">Vol. 3, No. 9, September 1978</a></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Byte_Magazine&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" title=\"Edit section: Vol. 3, No. 9, September 1978\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.devili.iki.fi/library/author/1504.en.html\">James M. Williams</a> (<b>1978</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://archive.org/stream/byte-magazine-1978-09/1978_09_BYTE_03-09_Graphic_Manipulations#page/n83/mode/2up\">Antique Mechanical Computers, Part 3: The Torres Chess Automation</a></i>.&#160;» <a href=\"/El_Ajedrecista\" title=\"El Ajedrecista\">El Ajedrecista</a></li></ul>\n<p><span id=\"BYTE310\"></span>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Vol._3.2C_No._10.2C_October_1978\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://archive.org/details/byte-magazine-1978-10\">Vol. 3, No. 10, October 1978</a></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Byte_Magazine&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9\" title=\"Edit section: Vol. 3, No. 10, October 1978\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:126px;\"><a href=\"https://archive.org/details/byte-magazine-1978-10\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/0/01/223-front.gif\" width=\"124\" height=\"163\" class=\"thumbimage\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/File:223-front.gif\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Vol. 3, No. 10</div></div></div> \n<ul><li> <a href=\"/Dan_Spracklen\" title=\"Dan Spracklen\">Dan Spracklen</a>, <a href=\"/Kathe_Spracklen\" title=\"Kathe Spracklen\">Kathe Spracklen</a> (<b>1978</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://archive.org/stream/byte-magazine-1978-10/1978_10_BYTE_03-10_Chess_for_the_Microcomputer#page/n87/mode/2up\">First Steps in Computer Chess Programming</a></i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://archive.computerhistory.org/projects/chess/related_materials/text/4-4.First_Steps.Byte_Magazine/First_Steps_in_Computer_Chess_Programing.Spracklen-Dan_Kathe.Byte_Magazine.Oct-1978.062303035.sm.pdf\">pdf</a> from <a href=\"/The_Computer_History_Museum\" title=\"The Computer History Museum\">The Computer History Museum</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Norman_Whaland\" title=\"Norman Whaland\">Norman Whaland</a> (<b>1978</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://archive.org/stream/byte-magazine-1978-10/1978_10_BYTE_03-10_Chess_for_the_Microcomputer#page/n167/mode/2up\">A Computer Chess Tutorial</a></i>. Reprinted (<b>1988</b>) in <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Compendium\" title=\"Computer Chess Compendium\">Computer Chess Compendium</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Peter_W._Frey\" title=\"Peter W. Frey\">Peter W. Frey</a>, <a href=\"/Larry_Atkin\" title=\"Larry Atkin\">Larry Atkin</a> (<b>1978</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://archive.org/stream/byte-magazine-1978-10/1978_10_BYTE_03-10_Chess_for_the_Microcomputer#page/n181/mode/2up\">Creating a Chess Player</a>.</i> An Essay on Human and Computer Chess Skill, pp. 182-191. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://archive.computerhistory.org/projects/chess/related_materials/text/3-3.Creating_A_Chess_Player/Creating_A_Chess_Player.Frey_Atkin.Byte_Magazine.Oct-1978.062303029.pdf\">pdf</a> from <a href=\"/The_Computer_History_Museum\" title=\"The Computer History Museum\">The Computer History Museum</a></li>\n<li> <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://archive.org/stream/byte-magazine-1978-10/1978_10_BYTE_03-10_Chess_for_the_Microcomputer#page/n191/mode/2up\">What's New? Computer chess; Microchess 1.5; Boris</a></i>, pp. 193, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://archive.computerhistory.org/projects/chess/related_materials/text/4-1%20and%204-2.Whats_New_Byte_Magazine/Whats_New.Microchess_1-5.Boris.Byte_Magazine.Oct-1978.062303032.pdf\">pdf</a> from <a href=\"/The_Computer_History_Museum\" title=\"The Computer History Museum\">The Computer History Museum</a>&#160;» <a href=\"/MicroChess\" title=\"MicroChess\">MicroChess</a>, <a href=\"/Boris\" title=\"Boris\">Boris</a></li></ul>\n<p><span id=\"BYTE311\"></span>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Vol._3.2C_No._11.2C_November_1978\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://archive.org/details/byte-magazine-1978-11\">Vol. 3, No. 11, November 1978</a></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Byte_Magazine&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10\" title=\"Edit section: Vol. 3, No. 11, November 1978\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<ul><li> <a href=\"/Dan_Spracklen\" title=\"Dan Spracklen\">Dan Spracklen</a>, <a href=\"/Kathe_Spracklen\" title=\"Kathe Spracklen\">Kathe Spracklen</a> (<b>1978</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://archive.org/stream/byte-magazine-1978-11/1978_11_BYTE_03-11_The_Sky_is_the_Limit#page/n17/mode/2up\">An Exchange Evaluator for Computer Chess</a></i>. &#160;» <a href=\"/Static_Exchange_Evaluation\" title=\"Static Exchange Evaluation\">SEE</a>, <a href=\"/SOMA\" title=\"SOMA\">SOMA</a></li>\